Description of non-type material. Two specimens from River Kashaf share with holotype and the paratypes most diagnostic features. Thus, they have a completely scaleless sharp ventral keel, – 4.2 teeth on the right 5 th ceratobranchial, an upturned mouth, 8 ½ branched dorsal-fin rays, 13 ½ and 14 ½ anal-fin branched rays, 41 ( 20 + 21 ) total vertebrae and 13 predorsal abdominal vertebrae (
